contentrichtext.text: '''V1''', '''V01''' or '''V-1''' can refer to version one (for anything) (e.g., see [[version control]]) '''V1''', '''V01''' or '''V-1''' may also refer to: {{TOC Right}} ==In aircraft and vessels== * [[V1 speed|V<sub>1</sub> speed]], the maximum speed at which an aircraft pilot may abort a takeoff without causing a runway overrun * [[Fokker V.1]], a German sesquiplane experimental fighter prototype, built in 1916 * [[LNER Class V1/V3]], an 1930–1939 British 2-6-2 tank engine * [[Vultee V-1]], an American single-engine airliner of the 1930s * USS V-1, 1924–1931 designation of the [[USS Barracuda (SS-163)|USS ''Barracuda'' (SS-163)]], first of the US "V-boat" series of submarines * V1, the Polynesian ''va’a hoe'' rudderless single-paddler [[outrigger canoeing|outrigger canoe]] ==In anatomy== * V1, the [[Visual cortex#Primary visual cortex (V1)|primary visual cortex]] * V<sub>1</sub>, the [[ophthalmic nerve]], first division of the trigeminal nerve ==In entertainment and media== * Virgin1, the 2007–2010 name of the British television channel ''[[Channel One (UK TV channel)|Channel One]]'' (which ceased to exist in 2011) ==In linguistics== * [[Base form]] (V<sub>1</sub>) of an English [[verb]]. ** [[Past simple]] form (V<sub>2</sub>) of an English [[verb]]. ** [[Past participle]] form (V<sub>3</sub>) of an English [[verb]]. ==In places== * [[V1 (building)]], a skyscraper in Sheffield * [[V1 Gallery]], in Copenhagen ==In science== * [[ATC code V01]] ''Allergens'', a subgroup of the Anatomical Therapeutic Chemical Classification System ==In technology== * [[V-1 flying bomb]] or ''buzzbomb'', a World War II German weapon * [[V.1]], a telephone communications standard of the ITU-T * [[V1 Ltd]], A [[document management]] software company ==See also== * [[VI (disambiguation)]] (letter "i" as opposed to number "1") {{Letter-NumberCombDisambig}}
